commit.message: Add ryu and tikv to trophy case

Don't use the word 'unwrap' to describe core unwrapping functions

It's tautological, and Rust-specific Jargon.

This changes various Option/Result methods to consistently describe unwrapping
behavior using the words "return", "contain", "consume".

It also renames the closure argument of `Return::unwrap_or_else` to `default` to
be consistent with `Option`.
Reorder declarations of Result::expect_err/unwrap_err to match Option
Reorder declarations of Result::export/unwrap to match Option
librustc_lint: In recursion warning, change 'recurring' to 'recursing'
Fix setting PATH during linkage on windows-gnu
Convert HashMap to BTree in build-manifest
Add a test that -fPIC is applied

Update relnotes for 1.15.1

I already checked this into stable, but it needs to be on master/beta too.

rustc: Remove all "consider using an explicit lifetime parameter" suggestions

These give so many incorrect suggestions that having them is
detrimental to the user experience. The compiler should not be
suggesting changes to the code that are wrong - it is infuriating: not
only is the compiler telling you that _you don't understand_ borrowing,
_the compiler itself_ appears to not understand borrowing. It does not
inspire confidence.

Delete the llvm submodule lockfile when configuring on the bots

This should fix the periodic error that .git/modules/src/llvm/index.lock
exists on the mac slaves.
